      <div xml:id="NA95-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu talaivaṉ (EN, EV: talaimakaṉ; ET: talaimakaḷ) pāṅkaṟku ivviṭattu ittaṉmaittu (EV: ittaṉmaiyatu) eṉa uraittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how HE said to [his] companion “this is the nature of this place”.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA95">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kaḻaipā ṭiraṅkap palliyaṅ kaṟaṅka</l>
<l>            vāṭumaka ṇaṭanta koṭumpuri nōṉkayiṟ</l>
<l>            ṟatavat tīṅkaṉi yaṉṉa cemmukat</l>
<l>            tuyttalai manti vaṉpaṟaḻ tūṅkak</l>
<l>            kaḻaikka ṇirumpoṟai yēṟi vicaitteḻuntu </l>
<l>            kuṟakkuṟu mākka ṭāḷaṅ koṭṭumak</l>
<l>            kuṉṟakat tatuvē kuḻumiḷaic cīṟūr</l>
<l>            cīṟū rōḷē nāṟumayirk koṭicci</l>
<l>            koṭicci kaiyakat tatuvēpiṟar</l>
<l>            viṭuttaṟ kākātu piṇittaveṉ ṉeñcē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>It [is] inside those hills,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the little hill people, mounting speedily up(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ēṟi vicaittu eḻuntu</term>: how to account for this apparent redundancy? Does is refer to the process of a mass of people clambering up the hill? (Actually the less well attested variant <term xml:lang="ta">niṉṟu</term> is preferable, while <term xml:lang="ta">vicaittu eḻuntu</term> looks like a gloss of <term xml:lang="ta">ēṟi</term>.)</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">the big height of the bamboo area, clap the tact,</l>
<l rend="indent">when the strong young one of the cotton-headed she-monkey,</l>
<l rend="indent">[its] face as red as the sweet ripe fruit of the country fig, hangs on</l>
<l rend="indent">the durable rope of twisted strands that has been walked by</l>
<l rend="indent4">the dancing girl,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while the singing of the bamboo [flute] sound [and] many</l>
<l rend="indent2">instruments sound</l>
<l rend="indent4">– the little village with an enclosure for [their] herd(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">kuḻu miḷai</term>: this foot has several variants such as <term xml:lang="ta">koḻu miḷai</term>, a "rich enclosure", and <term xml:lang="ta">koṭu miḷai</term>, a "bent enclosure", which is likewise not very convincing (the <term xml:lang="ta">koḻu miṉai</term> of ETv probably is a misreading).</note>.</l>
<l>She [is] from the little village,</l>
<l rend="indent4">the creeper woman with fragrant body hair.</l>
<l>It [is] in the palm of the hand of the creeper woman,</l>
<l rend="indent3">my heart that has been fettered, not to be set free by others.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="9f.B">
    <l>It is in the palm of the hand of the creeper woman.</l>
    <l>What has fettered [my] heart ... ?</l>
</lg>
        </lg>
